review:
Even though I've had this game for a few months now and have purchased copies for at LEAST five other friends, I never wrote a review because it had that seductive "overwhelmingly positive" tag and I felt everything I could say had been said. But after 10000 reviews, it sadly has dropped to "very positive" and my time has come to aid in the climb back. My review can be summarized in four words. THIS GAME F***ING ROCKS. I'll admit I'm a sucker for roguelikes, but Gunfire scratches every last itch with a smooth, fast-paced FPS scaffolding and an incredible dev team CONSTANTLY pushing out amazing content updates including patches suggested by the community. In a sea of bullcrap early-access drivel, Gunfire Reborn stands as a beacon that early access exists for a reason. This game is a blast alone or with friends, keeps getting better and better, and comes at a VERY affordable price tag. There's nothing else to say. If you even have a hint of desire to try this game out, just buy it. These types of developers are the ones who deserve our hard-earned money. I legitimately put this up there with the likes of Cogmind, Synthetik, and Hades as setting the bar for what we should expect in an early access roguelike. 

TLDR;
Buy this game. Buy copies for your friends. It is a game that you will keep coming back to no matter how many $60 AAAA blockbuster games you shove into your steam library. Hats off to this small dev team for punching miles above their weight class.

